parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded. It can also lead to further damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: transmission shifts out of gear intermittently

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective engine mounts can cause excessive engine movement, leading to premature wear on other engine components, and potentially causing the engine to stall or lose power, which can increase the risk of accidents.

A cracked piston ring can cause a loss of compression, leading to engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing the engine to stall or fail, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Engine stalling due to overheating can cause a loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
Engine failure can cause a loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, and leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the ECU can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, as well as engine fires.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on and stays on
smoke and flames appear under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on and stays on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inertia seat belt can lead to inadequate restraint of the driver or passenger, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not lock when jerked
the seat belt fails to hold the driver or passenger in place during an accident
the seat belt does not retract properly
the seat belt allows excessive movement of the driver or passenger during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the jack can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage while changing a tire or performing maintenance, compromising vehicle safety and operation.
symptoms: The jack buckles or breaks in half while in use
making it difficult or impossible to lift the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner can lead to discomfort, distraction, and decreased visibility while driving, potentially affecting vehicle safety and operation.
symptoms: The air conditioner fails to cool or blows warm air
reducing the overall comfort and driving experience.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design and location of the license plate can cause injuries, particularly to children, who may come into contact with the protruding plate while climbing on or around the vehicle.
symptoms: The license plate sticks out from the bumper
creating a hazard for children or individuals who may come into contact with it.
